OL,3,CEverything you need to know about the
OL,4,Cgovernment's asylum shake-up
OL,6,FThe government has committed to ending
OL,7,Fthe use of hotels to house asylum
OL,8,Fseekers by 2029, with an ambition to
OL,9,Fdo so sooner than that.
OL,11,FThey say the hotels can be a "pull
OL,12,Ffactor" encouraging people to come to
OL,13,Fthe UK, with smugglers using the
OL,14,F"prospect of a paid-for hotel" to
OL,15,F"lure asylum seekers into small boats".
OL,17,FTo replace the hotels, the government
OL,18,Fis moving towards the use of large
OL,19,Fsites, including former military
OL,20,Fsites, as asylum accommodation.
